    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Analyzing the source of fuel used by households for daily lighting in the Sub-Metropolitan City, it was found that out of a total of 34,565 households, 33,584 (97.16%) use electricity, 345 (1.00%) use solar, 417 (1.21%) use kerosene, 20 (0.06%) use bio gas, and 199 (0.58%) use other fuel sources. Detailed ward-wise information is presented in the table."
